The paper deals with the IT security of connectionist AI applications, focusing on threats to integrity. It discusses AI-specific vulnerabilities such as adversarial attacks and poisoning attacks, which are relevant to the sub-category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also covers aspects such as interpretability, robustness, and documentation, which are relevant to the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically mentions computer vision applications, which are relevant to the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the AI supply chain, which includes planning, data acquisition, training, evaluation, and operation phases, and the need for multiple measures on different levels to achieve a minimum level of IT security, which are relevant to the sub-category of software engineering (cs.SE).
